  "rationale": "Section order follows the brief's scroll: an inverse hero bookend carries the ONLY accent via the sanctioned display-title-over-media (full-bleed Web-gallery-1 with a surface-toned scrim), then every following band is a light primary/panel field with no accent, alternating cream and espresso for rhythm via hard cuts only. Because the base style is offGridExpansion=LOCKED, no section is novel and no off-grid treatment (stagger/overlap/bleed/float-wrap) is applied on non-hero bands: the about, mission, visit and newsletter runs reuse the anchored-statement split on the grid; gallery reuses the full-bleed counter band with only a marginal caption; the curator quote reuses the portrait collage with a marginal caption; heritage adapts the icon-label grid into a four-era timeline as a single repeatable card run. ghost-word ('ABOUT', '1941 2023') is used as style identity (flag-independent) low-opacity behind content so text keeps contrast. The mission, heritage, visit and newsletter needs are met by adapting existing seeds rather than inventing structure, honoring reuse-before-create and every WoodWave neverDo (no buttons \u2014 all CTAs are typographic links; underline-only form field; no cards on cream \u2014 the timeline sits on primary with open cells; single accent confined to the hero)."
